{"ts":"2026-05-02T06:48:21.552Z","author":"audit-agent","op":"comment_add","patch":[{"op":"replace","path":"/front_matter/updated_at","value":"2026-05-02T06:48:21.552Z"},{"op":"add","path":"/front_matter/comments","value":[{"created_at":"2026-05-02T06:48:21.552Z","author":"audit-agent","text":"Audit 2026-05-02: listAllDocuments reads all files from all type directories, parses each with TOON/JSON parser, runs onRead hooks, then deduplicates by ID. For 636+ items this is O(n) reads. A manifest-based approach (tracking id->path->mtime) would enable incremental reads. Calendar listAllFrontMatter has the same issue. Sentry lazy-loading confirmed working (ensureSentryInit with _initDone guard). Embedding batch retry with exponential backoff confirmed correct."}]}],"before_hash":"bd1d39438db78da9b88944a3a0082ec9c7c50fde43b073a13532a66fa69a60db","after_hash":"67e881f5ddd8c57b618f34661490af643c1a6ab36d492ebb90f9c3bbc4c65708"}
